=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Engine => Str

Indicates the type of Amazon Polly voice that Amazon Lex should use for
voice interaction with the user. For more information, see the
C<engine> parameter of the C<SynthesizeSpeech> operation
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/polly/latest/dg/API_SynthesizeSpeech.html#polly-SynthesizeSpeech-request-Engine)
in the I<Amazon Polly developer guide>.

If you do not specify a value, the default is C<standard>.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> VoiceId => Str

